{"id": 237084666, "title": "Adamawa gov reshuffles cabinet, warns against sabotage", "text": "Determined to ensure that his government effectively commits to its eight-point agenda, Governor Ahmadu Fintiri, has reshuffled his cabinet. A press statement issued in Yola and signed by Chief Press Secretary, Humwash Wounosikou stated that the minor cabinet reshuffle is to optimise the administration\u2019s performance. The reshuffle affected four ministries \u2013 Neido Geoffrey Kufulto, former Commissioner for Information, now takes charge as Commissioner for Women Affairs; Wunfe Anthony moves to the Ministry of Transportation; James Iliya, previously Commissioner for Entrepreneurship, takes over as Commissioner for Information and Hamajumba Gatugel is now in charge as Commissioner for the Ministry of Entrepreneurship. Fintiri who expressed confidence in his commissioners\u2019 ability to deliver on their new responsibilities, stressed, \u201cThis reshuffle is designed to maximise our team\u2019s strengths and improve services to the people of Adamawa State.\u201d The governor warned against acts of sabotage and urged the commissioners to discharge their duties diligently. He also tasked the affected commissioners to work together for a seamless transition, urging that they should continue to serve the state with total dedication and commitment to duty.", "summary": "<p>Determined to ensure that his government effectively commits to its eight-point agenda, Governor Ahmadu Fintiri, has reshuffled his cabinet. A press statement issued in Yola and signed by Chief Press Secretary, Humwash Wounosikou stated that the minor cabinet reshuffle is to optimise the administration\u2019s performance. The reshuffle affected four ministries &#8211;\u00a0 Neido Geoffrey Kufulto, former </p>\n <br/> <a href='https://punchng.com/adamawa-gov-reshuffles-cabinet-warns-against-sabotage/'>Read More</a>", "url": "https://punchng.com/adamawa-gov-reshuffles-cabinet-warns-against-sabotage/", "ima